WEBVTT

00:00.996 --> 00:02.356
Agh!

00:06.099 --> 00:07.250
Agh!

00:07.338 --> 00:09.601
Are you sure you don't
want any help with that?

00:10.005 --> 00:12.056
I fit my high school best
friend into a suitcase

00:12.144 --> 00:14.272
way smaller than this when
we were crossing the border

00:14.360 --> 00:15.512
between Laos and Vietnam,

00:15.600 --> 00:18.204
so I'm pretty sure
I can figure this out.

00:18.478 --> 00:21.350
Ooh, I can't wait to get
to the Galapagos and like,

00:21.437 --> 00:23.491
breathe the sea air
and get my...

00:23.579 --> 00:24.554
Beach curls back.

00:24.649 --> 00:26.668
Yeah, you've mentioned that
a couple times.

00:27.146 --> 00:28.749
Are you still trying
to close that thing?

00:28.836 --> 00:30.474
- Agh!
- Boys, it looks like

00:30.562 --> 00:33.143
I won't be able to see that
wedding venue with you today,

00:33.231 --> 00:34.755
your mother's had a bit
of a relapse.

00:34.915 --> 00:36.800
Take it the "Crows" movie
is still shelved.

00:36.887 --> 00:38.862
I'm sorry, we've started
looking at wedding venues

00:38.950 --> 00:40.586
and no one chose to tell me?

00:40.674 --> 00:43.535
Touring a wedding venue is
an incredibly intimate thing

00:43.623 --> 00:45.069
and we wanted to keep it small.

00:45.157 --> 00:46.300
You invited Dad.

00:46.388 --> 00:49.260
Okay, I don't know what that's
supposed to mean, Alexis.

00:49.348 --> 00:50.828
<i>John, something's
happening!</i>

00:50.916 --> 00:53.917
Coming, Moira.
Don't make any sudden moves.

00:54.499 --> 00:56.168
Okay, you should probably
stay here.

00:56.255 --> 00:57.604
No, you shouldn't-
Okay.

01:00.164 --> 01:03.739
John, remind me
to reprimand that latch,

01:03.827 --> 01:05.869
it's been awfully moody today.

01:05.957 --> 01:08.362
Well, good-good morning,
Sweetheart.

01:08.481 --> 01:10.268
Look who's come to see you.

01:10.356 --> 01:13.925
Finally. I'll have
the continental breakfast

01:14.012 --> 01:16.997
with the fresh-squeezed
grapefruit juice.

01:17.085 --> 01:18.850
Orange Pekoe tea.

01:18.938 --> 01:21.636
No, Moira, Moira,
it's-it's David and Patrick.

01:21.717 --> 01:23.458
- Um?
- Don't we have something

01:23.547 --> 01:24.959
- we want to say?
- Yes,

01:25.047 --> 01:26.485
thank you, John.

01:26.680 --> 01:29.814
Sadly, I won't be able
to squire you

01:29.902 --> 01:33.073
for today's wedding venue
peregrination.

01:33.161 --> 01:34.585
You invited Mom?

01:34.734 --> 01:37.215
She's literally been asleep
in a closet for a week.

01:37.303 --> 01:39.218
Just know that missing this

01:39.306 --> 01:42.593
will be the heavy-hearted
part of my day.

01:42.681 --> 01:44.616
Okay, does nobody care
that I'm going to be gone

01:44.704 --> 01:45.803
- for six months?
- Yes,

01:45.900 --> 01:47.299
of course we care,
Honey.

01:47.387 --> 01:49.536
- Don't we, Moira?
- Take me with you.

01:49.624 --> 01:50.778
Okay. On that note,

01:50.866 --> 01:52.532
I think we should get you
out of the room.

01:52.620 --> 01:53.900
Alexis, you are more than
welcome

01:54.005 --> 01:56.902
- to come see the place with us.
- Thank you.

01:56.990 --> 01:58.697
That actually works out super
well for me

01:58.785 --> 02:00.015
because you guys
can just drive me, straight

02:00.103 --> 02:02.692
to the airport after.
Hm-hm-hm.

02:03.902 --> 02:05.584
- See what you've done there?
- Yeah.

02:05.672 --> 02:07.691
Mhmm.
Out. Out, out, out.

02:08.562 --> 02:10.562
